{
  "text": "We mapped spnA to the cytological region 99D01± 99E01 (Supplementary ®gure 2) . The Berkley Drosophila Genome Project predicted a Rad51-like gene (CG7948) to reside within this region of the genome. CG7948 shows strong sequence similarity to the yeast and mammalian Rad51 gene (see below). Since two other spindle-class genes, spnB and okra, encode members of the Drosophila Rad51 family and Rad54, respectively [CITATION_1] , CG7948 was a likely candidate for spnA. Sequence analysis of spnA alleles revealed unique missense mutations within CG7948 (Table I ). Thus, spindle-A encodes a Drosophila Rad51-like gene. ",
